HEADWORD: Amorist
<hw>Am"o*rist</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>armor</ets> love. See <er>Amorous</er>.]</ety> <def>A lover; a
gallant.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was the custom for an <qex>amorist</qex> to impress the name of
his mistress in the dust, or upon the damp earth, with letters fixed
upon his shoe.</q> <rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>A-mornings</ent>⟦br⟧
